Analysis of standard deviations
===============================
This analyses the distribution of the normalised deviations
Delta = (Ihl - Mn(Iothers) )/sqrt[sd(Ihl)**2 + sd(Mn(I))**2]
If the SD is a true estimate of the error, this distribution should have
 Mean=0.0 and Sigma=1.0 for all ranges of intensity

The analysis is repeated for ranges of increasing Imean
The Mean is expected to increase with Imean since the latter
is a weighted mean and sd(Ihl) & Ihl are correlated

If the Sigma increases with Imean, increase the value of SdAdd

ISa is the predicted asymptotic value of I/sd(I) for large I, see
 K.Diederichs, Acta Cryst. D66,733

SD corrections:- SdFac * Sqrt[sd(I)**2 + SdB I + (SdAdd I)**2]
